6:
Hey... No one said it was time for a
nap!
23: I see you two didn't hold back, eh?
38:
They're on the roof. If you hurry, you
can catch up...
45:
Actually, Sho, I don't like men that
way.
53:
So no, I don't like Ayumu
romantically.
57:
Wait, so... You're one of THOSE
people?
61:
Saying it like that is pretty rude, you
know. Seriously, your phrasing could
use some work.
65:
Uh, sorry... I just... Does this mean...
you like girls—er, women?
69:
I don't know. I've never had romantic
feelings for anyone my whole life.
72:
...What, is there some rule that says I
have to?
79: I was envious of you, actually.
82:
He saved me, and I looked up to him
for it, but I was always too
embarrassed to thank him...
86: Er... What are you talking about?
90:
Then we all entered high school, and
I got to be friends with you both...
94:
I started not caring about those
regrets.
97:
It was fun, hanging out with you
guys. I never wanted those days to
end...
101:
I'm sorry, Sho, for being too cowardly
to say these things earlier.
105:
Why... Why are you apologizing? I
just... I was being a selfish jerk...
112:
This time, though... I'll be the one to
save Ayumu.
130:
What was your name again?
Nagihara? You're late.
138:
Now I just need you to open the gate
and guide us away...
142:
We haven't found the lance yet!
Besides, the people of this city can't
cross the Rift!
146:
That's what the Dragon's Iris is for.
Give people powers, and they'll be
able to hold their own.
149:
Relax. We can put your family on the
list of people we're saving. All the
other trash out there can rot instead.
153:
What? You're not taking everyone
with you? Not even your friends?
158:
Still want to play the savior of the
world, huh?
180:
You want to save the trash so you
can feel better about yourself.
183:
Thanks for making this so easy for
me!
228: I'm not much of a hero, but I'm trying.
233:
Ayumu Nagihara. I've been waiting
for you.
237: Tell me where the Antipode Lance is.
240:
You knew about the lance when we
first met. You even knew about
Stella and the rest of us.
244:
And Mikoto Hoshino... He had the
same eyes as Stella and Nova!
249:
How fitting. I suppose you should be
the one to end it all.
264: It's time for us to wake...
269: No... We can't let them do this!
285:
An ancient dragon? No, it's not... But
then what is it?
289:
An eye that sees the stars... Just like
mine?
296:
The Antipode Lance has the power
to shatter worlds and join them
together. But it's nothing but a
fragment of the true beast and its
power!
300:
Oghir... It'll finally be ours—a world
where no one will be left behind!
309:
What are you so surprised about? A
goddess of the stars can freely
guide and discard the weapons she
makes!
312: Just like it was with you!
